## Interface Design

### API Design
* **Explicit over Implicit**: Make function signatures clear about what they accept and return.
* **Type Hints**: Follow type hint requirements in [python-style.mdc](code-style.mdc).
* **Documentation**: Follow docstring standards in [python-style.mdc](code-style.mdc).
* **Error Handling**: Use appropriate exception types. Document what exceptions functions may raise. See [standard-libraries.mdc](standard-libraries.mdc) for exception handling patterns.

### Abstraction Levels
* **Appropriate Abstraction**: Create abstractions at the right levelâ€”not too high (loses flexibility) or too low (loses clarity).
* **Interface Segregation**: Keep interfaces focused. Prefer multiple small interfaces over one large interface.
* **Default Implementations**: Use abstract base classes or protocols to define contracts while allowing default implementations.
